Future Feature — Kingdom Promotions

When a player reaches a new Standing, a ceremonial promotion screen will appear. Promotions are permanent account milestones and celebrate the player's growing legacy within their Kingdom. No gameplay bonuses are required initially; the ceremony itself is the reward.

### Future Feature — The Crownbound

The title of **Crownbound** is unique within each Kingdom.

Design goals:

- Only one player per Kingdom may hold the title at a time.
- Becoming Crownbound represents the highest honor beneath the reigning monarch.
- If another player surpasses the current Crownbound according to the future competition rules, the title may transfer.
- The exact succession, tie-breaking, inactivity, and challenge rules will be designed in a later phase.
- The Crownbound should be recognized throughout the game with unique visual presentation and future gameplay privileges.


### Future Feature — Crownbound Succession

- Only one account may hold the title of `Crownbound` within each Kingdom.
- A challenger must exceed the current Crownbound’s permanent Crown total by a meaningful succession margin.
- Surpassing the current holder by only one Crown is not sufficient.
- The exact succession margin, tie rules, inactivity rules, and transition ceremony will be designed when shared Kingdom rankings are implemented.
- Until multiplayer Kingdom rankings exist, reaching 50,000 Crowns may display `Crownbound` locally for progression testing.


